## Router Configuration

i configured one interface gig0/1 to be the network operations and assigned it an ip address of 
192.168.10.1 

### Interface Gig0/1 — Network Operations
commands used:
enable
configure terminal
interface gig0/1
ip address 192.168.10.1 255.255.255.0
no shutdown
exit

### Interface Gig0/2 — Finance

i configured one interface gig0/2 to be the finance  and assigned it an ip address of 
192.168.20.1 
commands used:
enable
configure terminal
interface gig0/2
ip address 192.168.20.1 255.255.255.0
no shutdown
exit

By default, all router interfaces are administratively down. The no shutdown command brings the interface up and makes it active.
Without it, the interface will not pass any traffic regardless of how correctly it is configured.
